## How to Test Your Page Locally

### Method 1: Direct Browser Opening (Easiest)
1. Find your HTML file in your file explorer/finder
2. Double-click the HTML file
3. It will open in your default web browser
4. To see changes: save your file, then refresh the browser (Ctrl+R or Cmd+R)

### Method 2: Drag and Drop
1. Open any web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
2. Drag your HTML file from file explorer into the browser window
3. Refresh after making changes

### Method 3: Right-Click Method
1. Right-click on your HTML file
2. Select "Open with" â†’ Choose your browser
3. Refresh to see updates

### Method 4: VS Code Live Preview (If Using VS Code)
1. Install "Live Server" extension in VS Code
2. Right-click your HTML file in VS Code
3. Select "Open with Live Server"
4. Page will auto-refresh when you save!

### What to Check
- [ ] Page loads without errors
- [ ] All text is visible
- [ ] Images appear (if added)
- [ ] Links go to the right pages
- [ ] Page looks okay on different browser sizes

### Common Issues
- **Images not showing?** Check your file path: `images/filename.png`
- **CSS not working?** Make sure it's linked: `<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">`
- **Links broken?** Use `.html` extension: `href="about.html"` not just `href="about"`
